The paper deals with online learning algorithms for sparse linear regression, which is a problem in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also makes use of the restricted isometry property, which is a concept from information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves computational efficiency and optimization, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with online learning in an adversarial setting, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
